## How to Attribute This Work

When using or adapting materials from this framework, please provide attribution as follows:

### For Organizations Using Templates/Policies
```
This [policy/template/tool] is based on the Federal Grant Compliance Framework 
by David Amoah Oduro (Gulf of Maine Research Institute), licensed under CC BY 4.0. 
Available at: https://github.com/damoahdao-cyber/federal-grant-compliance-framework
```

### For Academic Publications
```
Oduro, D. A. (2026). Federal Grant Compliance Framework: An open-source knowledge 
commons for nonprofit capacity building. GitHub. 
https://github.com/damoahdao-cyber/federal-grant-compliance-framework
```

### For Presentations
Include on a slide:
- Framework name: Federal Grant Compliance Framework
- Author: David Amoah Oduro, Gulf of Maine Research Institute
- License: CC BY 4.0
- Link: github.com/damoahdao-cyber/federal-grant-compliance-framework

### For Derivative Works
If you create a modified version:
```
This work is derived from the Federal Grant Compliance Framework by David Amoah Oduro,
licensed under CC BY 4.0. Modifications by [Your Name]. Original available at:
https://github.com/damoahdao-cyber/federal-grant-compliance-framework
```

